 # Changelog
 
+## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S7-P01-T078 (Visual/Motion Regression CI gate; NOT_DEPLOYED)
+
+- Seventy-eighth task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program. Turns the T077 frozen un-deletable-contract into a CI GATE: every UI PR runs the T077 detect_regression over the candidate worker source, and any change to the six-theme/motion identity BLOCKS the PR unless it carries an explicit approved-change record (element + a non-empty reason + an approver) -- so an accidental deletion of a theme or ambience layer is blocked while an intentional edit passes only when documented. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; pure gate logic over source hashes + one read-only GET, no worker/production/theme change; operational MODEL_SPEC untouched. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/visual_regression_ci.py: run_ci(baseline, candidate_src, approvals) -> decision (BLOCK / PASS / PASS_APPROVED), blocked_on, approved_changes + reasons, changed_by_category (visual vs motion), recording_checks (motion regressions), and documented thresholds (source hashes exact; a documented <=0.1% pixel tolerance for the screenshot layer). Aggregate roll-up hashes (master_visual, contract_root) are excluded from approvals so they cannot be used to blanket-allow a specific change. An independent skeptic found a FATAL false-negative -- THEME_JS (the client-side behaviour that runs the key motions blurTextIn/animateGauge/syncHeroVideo/reduced-motion), HEAD_INIT (the anti-flash theme bootstrap), and the base CSS fed only the aggregate master_visual with no specific hash, so gutting a key motion in THEME_JS PASSED the gate -- which is fixed by ADDITIVELY extending the shared T077 tool visual_baseline.py with specific theme_js/head_init/base_css/fx_css hashes (categorised motion for theme_js/head_init/fx_css); the extension leaves T077's master_visual and per-theme hashes unchanged (T077's verifier still passes) and the T077 manifest is regenerated to stay consistent (14->18 asset-hash keys, master_visual identical). A second same-class instance was then fixed (the ${HERO_CSS} injection token, which _base_css was stripping before hashing) and a partition self-check added (fx_css derived from the THEME_FX mapping + a partition_consistency assertion that every [data-theme=X]/.fx-X name in the CSS is registered), after which the skeptic enumerated all 136 ${...} interpolation tokens and a whole-file line-deletion fuzz and found ZERO remaining aggregate-only escapes -> CONFIRMED_SOUND. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S7-P01-T078/: visual_regression_ci_report.json, known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND). Acceptance verified (evidence/ADP-S7-P01-T078/test-results/visual_regression_ci_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0), the verifier re-deriving the T077 baseline independently and running the real gate: a theme deletion (forest) and an ambience-layer deletion (cosmos) each BLOCK (and all six themes + every fx layer / keyframe / hero video / DOM producer / reduced-motion rule block, with no false-negative), a benign non-visual edit PASSES (no over-blocking); a documented approved change passes with its reason recorded, while an approval with no reason, no approver, for the wrong element, or for an aggregate hash all still BLOCK; the thresholds are documented and motion regressions are surfaced in recording_checks. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0; 1 read-only GET. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
+
 ## 2026-07-17 Australia/Sydney - ADP V0.1 task ADP-S7-P01-T077 (freeze six-theme visual + key-motion baseline as an un-deletable contract; NOT_DEPLOYED)
 
 - Seventy-seventh task of the ADP V0.1 FINAL EXECUTION program; opens Stage S7 (UI/UX, Motion & Performance). Freezes the recently-restored six themes (warm/minimal/fresh/techno/cosmos/forest) and their ambience/motion layer as an UN-DELETABLE contract: a deterministic asset-hash baseline over the deployed worker's complete visual/motion surface. release_mode NOT_DEPLOYED; the task reads deploy/cloudflare/worker_cloud.js (the live build b189d3cc0703) plus two read-only GETs to verify the live contract, and changes no worker/production/theme code -- it only FREEZES the current state. New tool arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/tools/visual_baseline.py: extract_contract (theme rules, THEME_NAV/FX/HERO/HERO_VIDEO mappings, CSS/HERO_CSS/THEME_JS/HEAD_INIT/FX_LAYERS surfaces, reduced-motion rule, keyframes), asset_hashes (a MASTER visual hash over the whole surface (CSS+HERO_CSS+THEME_JS+HEAD_INIT+FX_LAYERS+the hero/dashboard DOM+blurChars/sparkSVG DOM producers+the PAGE shell that injects them+the heroSection() assembly wiring+the todayPage { hero } render pass+the THEME_OPTIONS enumeration+the hero-video asset bytes+mappings) so nothing in the theme/motion identity can change without detection, plus per-theme attribution hashes over every `[data-theme]` rule + its ambience `.fx-*` motion CSS, a SEPARATE reduced-motion hash, and keyframes/fx-layers/hero-css hashes), baseline_matrix (6 themes x 6 routes x 5 viewports = 180 cells), build_baseline, detect_regression. Deliverables under arxiv-daily-push/docs/pursuing_goal/v0_1/evidence/ADP-S7-P01-T077/: visual_baseline_manifest.json (matrix + asset hashes + screenshot/interaction-recording schema), known_gaps.md, and adversarial_review.md (review CONFIRMED_SOUND after seven HOLEs were fixed to cover the full theme/motion surface (the hero/dashboard DOM, the blurChars/sparkSVG DOM producers, the PAGE shell, the THEME_OPTIONS enumeration, the heroSection() assembly wiring, the hero-video asset bytes, the todayPage { hero } pass) and a vacuous live-check control was de-vacuoused). Acceptance verified for the machine-verifiable backbone (evidence/ADP-S7-P01-T077/test-results/visual_baseline_tests.txt, ACCEPTANCE = PASS, exit 0): the 6x6x5 matrix is complete; the six per-theme fingerprints are distinct and the coverage is not shallow (per-theme rule counts warm2/minimal7/techno7/cosmos3/forest12, ambience fx-rule counts cosmos11/minimal5/techno5); nineteen un-deletable-contract controls all flag a regression (delete a theme, mutate a token, change an fx mapping, change a hero video, change ambience-motion CSS, change a per-theme component rule, change HERO_CSS, change a keyframe, delete the hero <video>, rename the cosmos gauge arc, gut the blurChars DOM producer, recolour the sparkSVG DOM producer, remove the PAGE ${FX_LAYERS} injection, remove the PAGE ${THEME_JS} injection, delete a theme from THEME_OPTIONS, corrupt a THEME_OPTIONS key, change heroSection's return-wiring, swap a hero video's bytes, drop todayPage's { hero } pass), plus a theme-set consistency cross-check (THEMES == THEME_OPTIONS == THEME_NAV), while a benign non-visual edit does not; reduced-motion is recorded separately (own hash + recording variant, removal flagged). A live-contract check (test-results/live_contract_check.txt) confirms the live production site serves the full six-theme contract (all 6 token blocks, 4 fx layers, reduced-motion, mappings, hero videos). The final 'Owner 确认基线' is a HUMAN sign-off the implementer does NOT self-sign; this package is READY_FOR_OWNER_CONFIRMATION. Realtime not regressed (no deploy, live build b189d3cc0703 == T040). Cost (unknown != 0): production new_requests 0, D1 0, R2 0, model_calls 0, recurring cloud 0; 2 read-only GETs. Ends IMPLEMENTATION_READY_FOR_INDEPENDENT_VERIFICATION.
